The paper deals with wiretap coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) that involves ensuring secure communication over channels susceptible to eavesdropping (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of well-rounded lattices, which are a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and number theory (cs.NT). The simulations and code constructions involve coding theory (cs.IT) and computer networks (cs.NI).
